 Force===\n* [[George Marshall Griffith|Wing Commander George Marshall Griffith]] (1877\u20131946), Commandant of the [[Royal Flying Corps]] in India<ref name=\"autogenerated48\">{{cite web|url=https://livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk/community/5183/?page=48 |title=Community: Bedford Modern School - List of Old Bedford Modernians serving in HM Forces 1914 - 1918. &#124; Lives of the First World War |publisher=Livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk |date= |accessdate=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[Percy Robert Clifford Groves|Brigadier-General Percy Robert Clifford Groves]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1878\u20131959), Air Strategist<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\" />\n* [[Robert Dickinson Oxland|Air Vice-Marshal Robert Dickinson Oxland]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1889\u20131959), Group Commander in [[Bomber Command]] (1943\u201344)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n* [[Edye Rolleston Manning|Air Commodore Edye Rolleston Manning]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] [[Military Cross|MC]] (1889\u20131957), senior officer in the [[Royal Air Force]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=A1AfAQAAMAAJ&q=DSO+bedford+modern&dq=DSO+bedford+modern|title=The Aeroplane|accessdate=14 November 2015|year=1935}}</ref><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Air CDRE. E.J. Manning'', 29 April 1957, p.12</ref>\n* [[Charles Henry Elliott-Smith|Air Commodore Charles Henry Elliott-Smith]] [[Air Force Cross (United Kingdom)|AFC]] (1889\u20131994), senior officer in the [[Royal Air Force]]<ref name=\"autogenerated49\">{{cite web|url=https://livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk/community/5183/?page=49 |title=Community: Bedford Modern School - List of Old Bedford Modernians serving in HM Forces 1914 - 1918. &#124; Lives of the First World War |publisher=Livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk |date= |accessdate=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n* [[H.D. Harvey-Kelly|Major H.D.