y-Massingberd, ''Burke's Irish Family Records'' London, U.K.: Burkes Peerage Ltd, 1976</ref>\n* [[Ernest Dynes|Brigadier Ernest Dynes]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1903\u20131968) was [[Aide-de-camp]] to HM Queen [[Elizabeth II]] (1955\u201357)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n* [[Thomas Henry Scott Galletly|Brigadier Thomas Henry Scott Galletly]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO&bar]] [[Military Cross|MC]] (1905\u20131972), Commander of the 1st Brigade, [[Arab League]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\" />\n* [[Major-General Reginald Booth Stockdale]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1908\u20131979) Colonel Commandant, [[REME]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\" />\n* [[Peter Boughey|Lt.-Col. Edward Peter Fletcher Boughey]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1911\u20131986), [[Special Operations Executive]]<ref>Bedford Modern School. A.B.C. List. Easter Term 1923</ref>\n* [[Keith Burch|Major-General Keith Burch]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1931\u20132013)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n\n===Navy===\n* [[Willoughby Baynes Huddleston|Commander Willoughby Huddleston]] [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] (1866\u20131953), [[Aide-de-camp|ADC]] to [[John Sinclair, 1st Baron Pentland|Lord Pentland]], [[Governor of Madras]] (1912\u201319)<ref name=\"auto2\"/><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Captain W.B. Huddleston'', 5 May 1953, p.8</ref>\n* [[Thomas Oloff de Wet|Captain Thomas Oloff de Wet]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1869\u20131940), Principal Naval Transport Officer during the [[Occupation of Constantinople|evacuation of Constantinople]] in 1923<ref>A Register of the Old Boys of the [[Bedford Modern School]]. Compiled and Edited by H.E. Vipan.  Published in [[Bedford]] by W.J. Robinson, 1900.  School Honours; p. ix</ref>\n* [[Alfred Ransom (Royal Navy officer)|Rear Admiral Alfred Ransom]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1871\u20131953), senior officer in the Royal Navy<ref>H.E. Vipan,''A Register of the Old Boys of the Bedford Modern School'' (Bedford, no date), p. 103</ref>\n* [[Sir Ernest Whiteside Huddleston]] [[Order of the Indian Empire|CIE]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] [[Royal Indian Navy|RIN]] (1874\u20131959), [[Aide-de-camp]] to the [[Governor-General of India|Viceroy of India]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\" />\n* [[Francis Walter Despard Twigg|Captain Francis Walter Despard Twigg]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1883-1951), senior officer in the Royal Navy<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk/community/5183/?page=13|title=Community: Bedford Modern School - List of Old Bedford Modernians serving in HM Forces 1914 - 1918. &#124; Lives of the First World War|website=livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk}}</ref>\n* [[Herbert Roff Newton|Commander Herbert Newton]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] [[Deputy Lieutenant|DL]] (1900\u20131973), [[Royal Navy]] Commander and [[Deputy Lieutenant]] of [[Bedfordshire]]<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\" />\n* [[Rear-Admiral Jack Kenneth Highton]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] (1904\u20131988), [[Aide-de-camp]] to Queen [[Elizabeth II]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\" />\n* [[Fred Stovin-Bradford|Captain Frederick Stovin-Bradford]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] [[Distinguished Service Cross (United Kingdom)|DSC&Bar]] (1919\u20131974), [[Royal Navy]] Commander ([[Fleet Air Arm]])<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\" />\n* [[Sir Ted Horlick|Vice-Admiral Sir Ted Horlick]] [[Order of the British Empire|KBE]] (born 1925), Director General of British Ships (1979\u201383), Chief Naval Engineer Officer (1981\u201383)<ref name=\"Underwood 2010\" />\n\n==Industry and commerce==\n[[File:John Howard (1791\u20131878), Mayor of Bedford.jpg|thumb|115px|right|[[John Howard (industrialist)|John Howard]]]]\n[[File:Arthur John Carter - Queensland Politician.png|thumb|115px|right|[[Arthur Carter (Queensland politician)|Arthur Carter]]]