innell]] [[Royal College of Physicians|FRCP]] [[Military Cross|MC]] (1878\u20131967), Consulting Physician<ref>{{cite web|url=http://munksroll.rcplondon.ac.uk/Biography/Details/2757|title=Munks Roll Details for John Wycliffe Linnell|work=rcplondon.ac.uk|accessdate=29 January 2015}}</ref><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Dr. John Wycliffe Linnell MC FRCP'', 12 December 1967, p.12</ref>\n* [[Henry Howarth Bashford|Sir Henry Howarth Bashford]] (1880\u20131961), Honorary Physician to King [[George VI]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://munksroll.rcplondon.ac.uk/Biography/Details/279|title=Munks Roll Details for Henry Howarth (Sir) Bashford|work=rcplondon.ac.uk|accessdate=29 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Adolphe Abrahams|Sir Adolphe Abrahams]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] (1883\u20131967), Olympic Medical Officer from 1912<ref>{{cite web|url=http://munksroll.rcplondon.ac.uk/Biography/Details/5|title=Munks Roll Details for Adolphe (Sir) Abrahams|work=rcplondon.ac.uk|accessdate=29 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[HLD Kirkham]] (1887\u20131949), Professor of Plastic Surgery [[Baylor University|Baylor University, Texas]], recipient of the US [[Legion of Merit]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tshaonline.org/handbook/online/articles/fki58|title=KIRKHAM, HAROLD LAURENS DUNDAS|work=tshaonline.org|accessdate=29 January 2015|date=2010-06-15}}</ref>\n* [[Frank Cook (surgeon)|Frank Cook]] [[FRCS]] [[FRCOG]] (1888\u20131972), [[Beit Memorial Fellowships for Medical Research|Beit Fellow]], [[obstetric]] and [[gynaecological]] surgeon<ref>{{cite web|url=http://livesonline.rcseng.ac.uk/biogs/E006234b.htm|title=Cook, Frank \u2013 Biographical entry \u2013 Plarr's Lives of the Fellows Online|work=rcseng.ac.uk|accessdate=29 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Basil Laver]] [[Master of Surgery|MS]] [[FRCS]] (1894\u20131934), surgeon<ref>{{cite web|url=http://livesonline.rcseng.ac.uk/biogs/E004335b.htm|title=Laver, Basil Leslie \u2013 Biographical entry \u2013 Plarr's Lives of the Fellows Online|work=rcseng.ac.uk|accessdate=7 March 2015}}</ref><ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Mr. B.L. Laver'', 31 December 1934, p 17c</ref>\n* [[Anthony Turner Andreasen|Professor Anthony Andreasen]] [[Royal Society of Edinburgh|FRSE]] [[Royal College of Surgeons of Edinburgh|FRCSE]] [[The International College of Surgeons|FICS]] (1906\u20131986), surgeon to the [[Governor-General of India|Viceroy of India]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/><ref>{{cite journal| pmc=1245335 | pages=318\u2013319 | volume=294 | issue=6567 | journal=Br Med J (Clin Res Ed) | title=OBITUARY | year=1987 | doi=10.1136/bmj.294.6567.318}}</ref>\n* [[George Godber|Sir George Edward Godber]], [[Order of the Bath|GCB]] (1908\u20132009), [[Chief Medical Officer (United Kingdom)|Chief Medical Officer]] for HM Government in England (1960\u201373)<ref>{{cite book|title=The Harpur Trust 1552\u20131973|author=Joyce Godber|year=1973|isbn=9780950291703}}</ref>\n* [[William Edward Lancaster]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] [[Order of Australia|AM]] (1909\u20132003), Chief Executive of the Royal Zoological Society of South Australia<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Joseph Graeme Humble|Professor Joseph Graeme Humble]] [[Royal Victorian Order|CVO]] [[Royal College of Physicians|FRCP]] (1913\u20131980), Professor of [[Hematology|Haematology]] at [[Westminster Hospital Medical School|Westminster Hospital]]<ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Prof. J.G. Humble'', 14 June 1980, p.16</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://munksroll.rcplondon.ac.uk/Biography/Details/2318|title=Munks Roll Details for Joseph Graeme Humble|work=rcplondon.ac.uk|accessdate=29 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Michael Tynan (cardiologist)|Professor Michael Tynan]] [[Doctor of Medicine|MD]] [[Royal College of Physicians|FRCP]] (born 1934), Professor of [[Paediatrics|Paediatric]] [[Cardiology]] at [[Guy's Hospital]] (1982\u201399)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://connection.ebscohost.com/c/articles/25468471/paediatric-cardiology-hall-fame-michael-john-tynan|title=The Paediatric Cardiology Hall of Fame \u2013 Michael John Tynan|work=ebscohost.com|accessdate=29 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Vaughan Robert Southgate|Dr Vaughan Southgate]] [[Deputy Lieutenant|DL]] [[Royal Society of Medicine|FRSM]] [[Fellow of the Linnean Society|FLS]] [[Society of Biology|FSB]] (born 1944), medical [[Parasitology|parasitologist]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.debretts.com/people-of-today/profile/25467/Vaughan-Robert-SOUTHGATE|title=Dr Vaughan Southgate, DL Authorised Biography \u2013 Debrett's People of Today|work=debretts.com|accessdate=30 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Henry Otto Br\u00fcnjes|Dr Harry Br\u00fcnjes]] (born 1954), Chairman of [[Premier Medical Group]], Governor [[Lancing College]], former Governor BMS<ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n* [[Mark Woodhead|Professor Mark Woodhead]] [[Royal College of Physicians|FRCP]] [[European Respiratory Society|FERS]] (born 1954), world authority on [[Respiratory tract infection|lung infection]] and [[pneumonia]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kongre2013.toraks.org.tr/eng/?p=mark_woodhead|title=Turkish Thoracic Society 16th Annual Congress|work=toraks.org.tr|accessdate=19 July 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Ian Martin Wylie|Dr Ian Martin Wylie]] [[Royal Society of Medicine|FRSM]] (born 1955), Chief Executive of the [[Royal College of Obstetricians and Gynaecologists]]<ref name=\"auto4\">''[[Who's Who (UK)|Who's Who 2016]]''.  Published by [[A & C Black|A&C Black Limited]], 2016</ref>\n* [[Michael Trudgill]] [[Aerospace Medical Association|FAsMA]] [[Royal Aeronautical Society|FRAeS]] (born 1966), [[Senior Medical Officer]] at the [[RAF Centre of Aviation Medicine]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.raf.mod.uk/rafbrizenorton/newsweather/index.cfm?storyid=2702A2DF-5056-A318-A843C332461FEF98|title=TOP AWARDS FOR RAF AEROSPACE MEDICINE DOCTORS|work=mod.uk|accessdate=20 May 2015}}</ref><ref>Aviation, Space, and Environmental Medicine, Vol. 83, No. 7, July 2012</ref>\n\n==Music==\n[[File:Max Richter - 2015 - ATP Festival (cropped).png|thumb|115px|right