orel|E.D. Morel MP]]]]\n[[File:Official portrait of Rt Hon Nick Gibb MP crop 2.jpg|thumb|115px|right|[[Nick Gibb|The Rt. Hon. Nick Gibb MP]]]]\n[[File:Official portrait of Richard Fuller MP crop 2.jpg|thumb|115px|right|[[Richard Fuller (Conservative politician)|Richard Fuller MP]]]]\n===Home===\n* [[James Howard (agriculturalist)|James Howard]] (1821\u20131889), [[Liberal Party (UK)|Liberal]] [[Member of Parliament|MP]]<ref name=\"worldcat.org1\"/>\n* [[William Robert Bousfield]] [[Queen's Counsel|KC]] [[Royal Society|FRS]] (1854\u20131943), [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]] [[Member of parliament|MP]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Arthur Pedley]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] (1859\u20131943), senior civil servant<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/>\n* [[Arthur Sheppard]] [[Royal Victorian Order|MVO]] (1862\u20131944), Private Secretary to the [[Archbishop of Canterbury]] (1902\u20131928)<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Archibald Dennis Flower|Sir Archibald Dennis Flower]] (1865\u20131950). Chairman of the [[Shakespeare Birthplace Trust|Trustees and Guardians of Shakespeare's birthplace]]<ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n* [[John Alfred Lawrence Billingham|Colonel John Alfred Lawrence Billingham]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] [[Royal Institution of Chartered Surveyors|FRICS]] (1868\u20131955), Chief Inspector of Works, [[War Office]] (1928\u201333)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/>\n* [[E. D. Morel|Edmund Dene Morel]] (1873\u20131924), [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]] [[Member of parliament|MP]]<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/>\n* [[Frederick Reginald Phipps|Major F. R. Phipps]] [[Order of the British Empire|OBE]] [[Institution of Civil Engineers|A.M. Inst. C.E.]] F.S.I. (1875\u20131927), Senior Engineering Inspector at the [[Department of Transport|Ministry of Transport]], 1924 to 1927<ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Major F. R. Phipps'', 12 January 1927, p.17</ref>\n* [[Sir Ralph Endersby Harwood]] [[Order of the Bath|KCB]] [[Royal Victorian Order|KCVO]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]