ir Francis Moncrieff Kerr-Jarrett]] (1885\u20131968), [[Custos Rotulorum]] of St James's, [[Jamaica]]<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Stanley Wyatt Smith]] (1887\u20131958), [[Consul (representative)|Consul-General]] of [[Manila]] (1938\u201342) and [[Honolulu]] (1943\u201344)<ref>Obituary in ''[[The Times]]'', ''Mr. S. Wyatt-Smith'', 19 November 1958, p.13</ref>\n* [[Ronald Okeden Alexander|Major-General Ronald Okeden Alexander]] [[Order of the Bath|CB]] [[Distinguished Service Order|DSO]] (1888\u20131949), Inspector General, Central Canada (1942\u201346)<ref name=\"Underwood 1981\"/>\n* [[Charles George Hawes|Charles Hawes]] [[Companion of the Indian Empire|CIE]] [[Military Cross|MC]] (1890\u20131963). Chief Engineer to the Government of [[Sind]]<ref>''Who was Who'' Vol. VI (1961\u201370) (London, 1972), p. 505</ref>\n* [[Frederick Williamson]] [[Order of the Indian Empire|CIE]] (1891\u20131935), [[Consul (representative)|Consul-General]] of [[Kashgar]] (1927\u201330)<ref name=\"Who Was Who\"/><ref>Obituary in ''The Times'', ''Mr Frederick Williamson'', 19 November 1935, p.19</ref>\n* [[Reginald Philip Abigail]] (1892\u20131969), [[District Commissioner (British Colonial)|District Commissioner]] of [[Rakhine State|Arakan]] during the [[Japanese conquest of Burma|fall of Burma]] in 1942<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=PKIWAQAAIAAJ&dq=reginald+abigail+burma+kellys&q=abigail+bedford+modern|title=Kelly's Handbook to the Titled, Landed and Official Classes|accessdate=14 June 2015|year=1969|last1=Kelly's}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=oCUbAQAAIAAJ&dq=punjab+bedford+modern&q=abigail+bedford+modern|title=The India Office and Burma Office List|accessdate=14 June 2015|year=1947}}</ref>\n* [[Bertram St. Leger Ten Broeke]] [[Order of the Indian Empire|CIE]] [[Military Cross|MC]] (1895\u20131962), Deputy Inspector-General of the Indian Police in [[Bihar]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://livesofthefirstworldwar.iwm.org.uk/story/84029|tit